    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-25T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="773"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.91/5109: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-26T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 26, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 26—2:50
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My April 23, 2 p.m. High Commission heard from British Minister who is returning
                    from Nanking today that Chinese Government is prepared to accept suggested
                    amendment to paragraph 11 of new draft resolution. That he has so informed his
                    Secretary for Foreign Affairs at Geneva and has told him that <persName
                        corresp="#p_WC1">Wang Ching-wei</persName> and the Chinese Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs have made it plain that this represents China’s last word and
                    limit of her concessions.</p>
                <p>Not repeated to Geneva.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
